The paper focuses on the relationship between visual and semantic similarity in the context of knowledge transfer, zero-shot learning, and semantic image retrieval, which are all related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of different similarity measures, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper examines the application of semantic methods, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
